{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c9fca124-7478-4746-9037-13fcf400f34d","content":"Here's what you need to change:\n\n### 1. Update packages in your `.csproj`\n\n**Remove:**\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk\" Version=\"...\" />\n```\n\n**Update:**\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"NUnit3TestAdapter\" Version=\"5.0.0\" />\n```\n(v5.0+ includes built-in Microsoft.Testing.Platform support)\n\n### 2. Enable the new platform\n\nAdd to your `.csproj`:\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n### 3. Run tests\n\n```bash\ndotnet test\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n- NUnit3TestAdapter **5.0+** ships with Microsoft.Testing.Platform natively — no extra packages needed.\n- `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` is **no longer required** and should be removed.\n- The `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>` property tells `dotnet test` to use the new platform instead of VSTest.\n- NUnit itself (`NUnit` package) stays unchanged.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"bc0c5063-b574-4e0f-a0a4-7f583c78b82b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating an NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a knowledge question - I can answer it directly without needing to explore any codebase.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer about the migration steps.","outputTokens":358,"requestId":"6806:24EAAB:293F0DC:2D8302F:69FD3379"},"id":"55d2d688-b96b-46a1-a424-87fcf0564f70","timestamp":"2026-05-08T00:51:14.446Z","parentId":"e9b73ceb-4128-4aab-b5d8-d8f9282b29b9"}
